OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1773876313
OL,3,CInside Tehran as filmmaker secretly
OL,4,Crecords life during Iran war
OL,6,FOver the ten days, Shirin shows a
OL,7,Fshift in the mood in Tehran. At first,
OL,8,Fpeople rejoice in the streets over the
OL,9,Fdeath of Ali Khamenei to the sound of
OL,10,Ffireworks.
OL,12,FUS and Israeli intervention was
OL,13,Fwelcomed at first, but as ordinary
OL,14,FIranians are killed and infrastructure
OL,15,Fbombed, Shirin begins to feel
OL,16,Fincreasingly despondent and questions
OL,17,Fthe point of this war.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/4
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
